stylometry: For class we used Data Clustering as our method of data mining. For my problem I took show results from 20 randomly selected 3 day eventing riders and averaged their individual scores as my data table. Then through excel equations, put in formulas that determined how each set of data varied from each cluster. After that I ran solver to find the different clusters of my data table, sorting the data into 5 groups of riders; excellent, good, average, poor, and awful. That way I could determine which group of riders from my data was the largest and what skill level of rider was most common.
